doc.previous: The Home Park adjoins the northern edge of the more extensive Windsor Great Park, occupying some 5,000 acres (2,020Â ha) [68] and including some of the oldest broadleaved woodlands in Europe.[69] In the Home Park, to the north of the castle, stands a private school, St George's, which provides choristers to the chapel. Eton College is located within about half a mile of the castle, across the River Thames.
